definition: any of various gems (as chrysoberyl or chalcedony) that reflect light when cut in a rounded shape

definition: a translucent mineral consisting of hydrated silica of variable color; some varieties are used as gemstones

name: black opal
definition: a dark colored opal with internal reflections of green or red

name: fire opal
definition: an opal with flaming orange and yellow and red colors

definition: a reddish opal with small patches of brilliant color

definition: a blue to grey green mineral consisting of copper aluminum phosphate

definition: the hard stony skeleton of a Mediterranean coral that has a delicate red or pink color and is used for jewelry

definition: an azure blue semiprecious stone
